anus.\" [ISBN:0-683-40008-8, MP:0002669, Wikipedia:Scrotum]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsubset: uberon_slim\nxref: BTO:0003098\nxref: CALOHA:TS-2341\nxref: EMAPA:19296\nxref: FMA:18252\nxref: GAID:393\nxref: galen:Scrotum\nxref: MA:0000409\nxref: MESH:D012611\nxref: NCIT:C12785\nxref: SCTID:265794003\nxref: UMLS:C0036471 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Scrotum\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Scrotum\nis_a: UBERON:0034929 ! external soft tissue zone\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0011756 {source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! male genital swelling\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:32525 ! Theria <mammals>\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0004053 ! external male genitalia\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a6/Scrotum_warm_and_cold.jpg\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3e/HairedHumanScrotum.png/200px-HairedHumanScrotum.png\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: has_relational_adjective \"scrotal\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In elephants the testes remain in the abdomen\" xsd:string {source=\"PMC1570914\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:9780\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In hedgehogs the testes remain in the inguinal canal\" xsd:string {source=\"PMC1570914\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:9363\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In humans and some other mammals, the base of the scrotum becomes covered with pubic hair at puberty\" xsd:string {taxon=\"NCBITaxon:9606\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In marsupials, the scrotum is not homologous to the eutherian scrotum, and development is under the control of X-linked genes, not androgens\" xsd:string {source=\"PMID:10984412\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:9263\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In marsupials, the scrotum is positioned in the caudal area of the abdomen, in the same position as the pouch in females. It has been suggested that the pouch and marsupial scrotum are sexual homologs, but it is more likely they arise from different primordia in the same morphogenetic field\" xsd:string {source=\"ISBN:113945742X\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:9263\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"The scrotum of marsupials is not homologous with the scrotum of mammals[ISBN:113945742X]\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015479\nname: scrotum skin\ndef: \"A zone of skin that is part of a scrotum.\" [OBOL:automatic]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"scrotal skin\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"skin of scrotum\" EXACT [FMA:20432]\nxref: EMAPA:36411\nxref: FMA:20432\nxref: MA:0003093\nxref: SCTID:361710000\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000014 ! zone of skin\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001300 ! scrotum\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Finds scrotum term","truncated":false},"title":"Finds scrotum term","time":{"start":1778379878986,"end":1778379878988}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_039deeffcafbd67b0169ffec66cc708192acfee6e66131bac4"}},"id":"prt_e0fb37204001d3R1QJiJJSHGy2","sessionID":"ses_1f04e18f6ffeknDO0yruVR5Ezz","messageID":"msg_e0fb34165001ztORlu7hkwJ4tb"}}
